> Cook it once, eat it twice: tonight's dinner extras transform into tomorrow's lunch. 
> That's thanks to special added ingredients that can easily be heated up, even at the office 
> (your coworkers will be amazed, trust us). It all starts out with a pizza party the night before, 
> with sausage, mozzarella, and yellow squash on a flatbread. The next day, the extra ingredients 
> are tossed with pasta for a desk lunch that you can be proud of.

> The nutrient information for the Veggie-Loaded Pasta Lunch is as follows:
> Calories 910, Fat 51 g, Saturated Fat 20 g, Cholesterol 110 mg, Sodium 1340 mg,
> Carbs 80 g, Fiber 6 g, Sugar 8 g, and Protein 35 g.

== Pizza ==

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat broiler to high or oven to 500 degrees with rack in upper position. Place @flatbreads{2} on a #baking sheet{} and let warm in broiler or oven as it preheats. Remove once golden brown, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Meanwhile, bring a #medium pot{} of salted water to a boil. Halve and peel @red onion{1}(peeled and halved), then cut into wedges. Core and seed @bell pepper{2}(cored and seeded), then cut into strips. Slice @yellow squash{1} into ½-inch-thick rounds. Mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}(minced).

Remove flatbreads from baking sheet and set aside. Toss squash, onion, and bell pepper with a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{4%teaspoon}. Place on same sheet, keeping each in their own section. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, and half the @Tuscan heat spice{1%tablespoon}. Broil or bake until tender and browned, ~{5-7%minutes}. (TIP: Keep an eye out for any burning.) Set aside once done.

Once water boils, add @gemelli pasta{6%ounce} to #pot{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Scoop out and reserve ¼ cup pasta cooking water, then drain.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Remove @Italian pork sausage{18%ounce} from casings; discard casings. Add sausage to pan, breaking meat into pieces with a #spatula{} or #wooden spoon{}. Cook until browned and no longer pink, ~{4-6%minutes}. Remove pan from heat.

Place flatbreads on another, lightly-oiled baking sheet. Spread ½ cup @crushed tomatoes{13.76%ounce} evenly over flatbreads (save the rest for step 5). Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Tear @mozzarella cheese{4%ounce} into small pieces with your hands and scatter over top. Evenly top flatbreads with half the sausage, half the onion, and all of the squash. Broil or bake until cheese melts and crust is crisp, ~{5-10%minutes}. Cut flatbreads into slices and serve.

== Pasta Lunch ==

Heat a drizzle of oil in pot used for pasta over medium-high heat. Add @garlic{2%cloves}(minced) and remaining Tuscan heat spice. Cook until fragrant, about ~{1%minute}. Add @chicken stock concentrate{1}, reserved pasta cooking water, and remaining sausage and tomatoes. Simmer until reduced slightly, ~{1-2%minutes}. Stir in gemelli, followed by @butter{1%tablespoon}. After stirring in butter, stir in bell pepper and remaining onion. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then remove pot from heat.

Divide pasta between two #reusable containers{}. Divide @parmesan cheese{1/4%cup} evenly and pack with containers, keeping it separate from the pasta. Keep refrigerated. When ready to eat, microwave pasta on high for ~{2-3%minutes}. Sprinkle with Parmesan before enjoying.